                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.1115/74a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="61" xml:id="d607fn61">Sent also to the Legation at Lisbon,
                        referring to telegram No. 24, July 26, 1 p.m.; to the U. S. S. <hi
                            rend="italic">Oklahoma</hi>, adding: “Advise <hi rend="italic"
                            >Quincy</hi>”; and to the Embassy at Madrid.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-26T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Inform Wendelin, American Embassy, Madrid, Department approves evacuation
                    Americans by train if obtainable to Valencia, provided in his judgment it is
                    feasible and provided Spanish Government guarantees safety of line and train and
                    provides adequate guard and all other necessary steps to ensure safety
                    Americans. He is authorized extend protection Austrians in his discretion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
